Package com.im.njams.sdk.communication.jms.factory

Interface JmsFactory

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActiveMqSslJmsFactory, AzureServiceBusJmsFactory, JndiJmsFactory
    public interface JmsFactory
extends AutoCloseable
    A named factory loaded via SPI for creating JMS related instances.
    Use find(Properties) for getting an instance.

    • Method Detail

      • find

        static JmsFactory find​(Properties settings)
        Tries to find a JmsFactory from SPI according to the given settings and using the following steps. Matches on getName() (ignoring case), simple class name or full-qualified class name.
        1. Use key "njams.sdk.communication.jms.jmsFactory" for SPI lookup
        2. Use key "njams.sdk.communication.jms.connectionFactory" for SPI lookup
        3. Use JndiJmsFactory as default.
        In the traditional scenario where only "njams.sdk.communication.jms.connectionFactory" is configured and is expected to be used for JNDI lookup for a ConnectionFactory instance, no additional configuration is necessary since the lookup done here will not find any matching JmsFactory and will use JndiJmsFactory as default, which works as before.

        When needing a non-JNDI implementation like ActiveMqSslJmsFactory or AzureServiceBusJmsFactory it's sufficient to specify the according SPI name in "njams.sdk.communication.jms.connectionFactory".

        The new "njams.sdk.communication.jms.jmsFactory" key is only needed, when implementing a different JNDI JmsFactory that still needs the common "njams.sdk.communication.jms.connectionFactory" key for looking the ConnectionFactory in the JNDI context as second step.
        Parameters:
        settings - Settings specifying what provider to use. Obtained from nJAMS' Settings.
        Returns:
        Found instance or JndiJmsFactory as a default. The returned instance is initialized with given settings.

      • getName

        String getName()
        Has to return a unique implementation name that is used for SPI lookup.
        Returns:
        Unique implementation name.

      • init

        void init​(Properties settings)
   throws javax.jms.JMSException,
          NamingException
        Is called to initialize this factory. After calling this, the factory is usable until close() is called.
        Implementations have to handle that this method could be invoked multiple times.
        Parameters:
        settings - The Njams instance's settings that uses this factory.
        Throws:
        javax.jms.JMSException - If creating a JMS object failed
        NamingException - If a JNDI related error occurred

      • createConnectionFactory

        javax.jms.ConnectionFactory createConnectionFactory()
                                             throws javax.jms.JMSException,
                                                    NamingException
        Is called for obtaining a ConnectionFactory instance. Once created, a factory should be reusable. So, it should be ok the return always the same instance.
        Returns:
        Has to return a ConnectionFactory instance.
        Throws:
        javax.jms.JMSException - If creating a JMS object failed
        NamingException - If a JNDI related error occurred

                                    String topicName)
                             throws javax.jms.JMSException,

      • close

        default void close()
        Is called when the factory is no longer used. Before using the same instance again, init(Properties) has to be called again.
        The default does nothing.
        Specified by:
        close in interface AutoCloseable
